data.description: ::::::: SUBMIT HIGHEST + BEST OFFERS BY 5pm SUNDAY ::::::  Step into the enchanting embrace of East Passyunk living with this classic rowhome that seamlessly blends history and modernity. Nestled in the heart of Philadelphia's most charming neighborhood, this gem invites you to a world where character and convenience converge.  As you approach, you’ll become smitten with Sigel St, a smaller, quieter street than most. The classic red-brick façade and stoop will beckon you in, setting the tone for the warmth that awaits. Enter through the front door into an open concept living/ dining area with a half bath. Continue through to the ample sized kitchen with tons of workspace and storage galore.  The outdoor space is S. Philly’s quintessential private oasis, a concrete back patio- perfect for al fresco dining or sipping your morning coffee.  Ascend the stairs to discover a bright sunlit front bedroom and two smaller bedrooms perfect for office, walk in dressing room/ closet, exercise space or nursery. There is a hall closet and a recently renovated full bath.  The basement is finished and provides useable storage, laundry area and extra living/ working space. An office, play room or art studio perhaps? Beyond the doorstep, East Passyunk beckons with its vibrant energy. Explore the eclectic mix of boutiques, renowned restaurants, and cozy cafes along the iconic Avenue. From cultural festivals to community events, this neighborhood is alive with a sense of community that adds value and richness to life. Walk to the Italian Market, BOK building and commute easily anywhere with public transportation.  This home is more than a dwelling; it's an invitation to immerse yourself in the enchantment of a neighborhood that captures the heart and soul of Philadelphia. The magic of East Passyunk could be right out your front door. What are you waiting for?
